## Applicability (read first)
Follow **all sections below** only when the **same user message** contains **`done`** and (**`full-scan`** OR **`full scan`**), case-insensitive.

If that combined trigger is **not** present, **ignore** this entire file for operational purposes.

## Scope (when applicable)
- Audit **`docs/**/*.md`**, prioritising **Microscopie**, **Determinatie**, **Honing**, then reference sections (mirror `mkdocs.yml` `nav`).
- Update drill content **only** in:
  - `docs/artificiele-pollen-test/snelle-pollen.md` — rapid presentation / speed drills
  - `docs/artificiele-pollen-test/verschillende-pollen.md` — contrast pairs/triads
  - `docs/artificiele-pollen-test/lastige-pollen.md` — difficult / noisy / ambiguous cases
  - `docs/artificiele-pollen-test/pollen-hints.md` — short diagnostic hint questions

## Content guidelines
- **snelle-pollen.md**: Short drill blocks; immediate classification prompt; answer key; one-line cue. Prefer existing image paths or `[to be verified]` placeholders if assets are missing.
- **verschillende-pollen.md**: Side-by-side contrasts; "what differs?" prompts; link to relevant `docs/` reference pages where grounded.
- **lastige-pollen.md**: Why the case is hard; what to attend to; common confusions — only if documented in sources you read.
- **pollen-hints.md**: Brief hint questions (apertures, ornamentation, size class, etc.); no fabricated species-level facts.

## Images from online databases
- Do **not** hotlink or embed third-party images without **license and stability** consideration.
- Prefer procedures or links documented in **`docs/online-databases/pollen-databases.md`** and allowed URLs in **`notes/_references.md`** (read-only; do not edit `notes/`).
- If no approved URL list exists in the repo, use **`[to be verified]`** and describe the *type* of image needed instead of inventing URLs.
